replies.bodyText:
No. I am proposing the following:
Rename KeyVersion to Version and move it off of key and put in on TableEntry. (It has to do with entries no keys after all) and have TableEntry extend Map.Entry.
Then on this class have:
CompletableFuture<TableEntry<KeyT, ValueT>> get(String keyFamily, KeyT key);
CompletableFuture<List<TableEntry<KeyT, ValueT>>> getAll(String keyFamily, List<KeyT> keys);
CompletableFuture<Version> put(String keyFamily, KeyT key, ValueT value);
CompletableFuture<List<Version>> putAll(String keyFamily, Iterable<Entry<KeyT, ValueT> items);
CompletableFuture<Version> putIfAbsent(String keyFamily, KeyT key, ValueT value);
CompletableFuture<Version> replace(String keyFamily, KeyT key, Version version, ValueT value);
CompletableFuture<List<Version>> replaceAll(String keyFamily, Iterable<TableEntry<KeyT, ValueT>> items);
CompletableFuture<TableEntry<KeyT, ValueT>> remove(String keyFamily, KeyT key);
CompletableFuture<Boolean> remove(String keyFamily, KeyT key, Version version);
CompletableFuture<Boolean> removeAll(String keyFamily, Iterable<TableEntry<KeyT, ValueT>> items);
In all of the above keyFamily may be null.

